      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "Florence2 Vision AI \u2014 Multi-Task Captioning\n\nUses Microsoft's Florence-2-large-ft model for image understanding tasks: captioning, object detection, segmentation, and OCR \u2014 all from one model.\n\nHow it works:\n1. LoadImage loads your input image\n2. DownloadAndLoadFlorence2Model downloads the model from HuggingFace on first run (~1.5 GB) and loads it in fp16 precision\n3. Florence2Run processes the image with the selected task (default: more_detailed_caption)\n4. PreviewImage shows the annotated output image\n5. PreviewAny displays the generated caption text\n\nTo try other tasks: Change the 'task' dropdown on Florence2Run. Options include caption, detailed_caption, ocr, referring_expression_segmentation, and more. Some tasks require text_input (e.g. segmentation needs a description of what to segment).\n\nRequires: ComfyUI-Florence2 (kijai)\nModel: microsoft/Florence-2-large-ft (auto-downloads)"
      ],
